## Taskbar Pinning Module — Commercial License Required

The following components are excluded from the open source license above and
are subject to a separate commercial license:

- The `TaskbarPinHelper` class and all its methods
- The `Invoke-TaskbarPin` function
- The `Update-PinButtonState` function
- The `$btnPin` control click handler
- Code directly responsible for writing to the Windows Taskband registry,
  constructing PIDL blob entries, injecting BEEF001D extension blocks, or
  acquiring the `TaskbarPinListMutex` system mutex, and anything
  for the purpose of programmatic taskbar pinning

Collectively referred to as the "Taskbar Pinning Module."

### Permitted Use (Free)

The Taskbar Pinning Module may be used free for:

- Personal, non-commercial use
- Educational and academic purposes
- Open source projects
- Evaluation and testing

### Commercial License Required

A paid commercial license is required to use the Taskbar Pinning Module in
any of the following contexts:

- Commercial software products (sold, licensed, or distributed for revenue)
- SaaS platforms, managed services, or hosted applications
- Any product or service generating direct or indirect revenue

For commercial licensing inquiries, contact: freenitial@gmail.com

